Preheat the oven to 200C/180C Fan/Gas 6. Line a large baking tray with baking paper.Mix all the ingredients together in a large bowl. Set aside for 15 minutes.Take small handfuls of the mixture and, using your hands, squeeze it over a sink or bowl to remove any excess moisture. Roll into a sausage shape and place on the baking tray. Repeat with the remaining mixture (you should have around 16 sausages).Bake for 25 minutes until golden-brown and cooked through.